cuicui_dsl is a macro (dsl!), while cuicui_chirp is a scene file format, parser and bevy loader. cuicui_chirp builds on top of cuicui_dsl, and has different features than cuicui_dsl. Here is a feature matrix: features cuicui_dsl cuicui_chirp statements & methods ‚úÖ ‚úÖ code blocks with in-line rust code ‚úÖ code calling registered functions ‚úÖ fn templates rust [1] ‚úÖ import from other files rust [2] hot-reloading ‚úÖ reflection-based methods ‚úÖ special syntax for colors, rules ‚úÖ lightweight ‚úÖ You may use cuicui_dsl in combination with cuicui_chirp, both crates fill different niches. A fn template is equivalent to defining a function that accepts an EntityCommands and directly calls dsl! with it # use cuicui_dsl::macros::__doc_helpers::*; // ignore this line pls
use cuicui_dsl::{dsl, EntityCommands}; fn rust_template(cmds: &mut EntityCommands, serv: &AssetServer) { dsl! { cmds, Root(screen_root column) { Menu(image(&serv.load("menu1.png"))) Menu(image(&serv.load("menu2.png"))) } }
} You can ‚Äî of course ‚Äî import functions from other files in rust and use that instead.

